# Retirement Risk Analysis — September 2026

*Created: June 2026 | Status: Draft*

---

## Purpose

This analysis models the financial risk of retiring in September 2026, with pension and CPP as the income floor (worst case), and maintaining current Stealth EA consulting income ($200,000/year) as the target scenario. The goal is to understand the gap, identify risks, and define mitigation strategies.

---

## Income Sources

| Source | Annual Amount | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Defined Benefit Pension | $45,750 | Begins September 2026 |
| CPP (Maximum) | $16,375 | ~$1,364/month; assumes age 65 eligibility |
| **Worst Case Floor** | **$62,125** | Pension + CPP only |
| Stealth EA Consulting | $137,875 (needed) | To reach $200K target |
| **Target Income** | **$200,000** | Maintains current lifestyle |

> **CPP Note:** The $16,375 figure reflects the 2024/2025 maximum. If taken before age 65, it is reduced by 0.6% per month early (up to 36% reduction at age 60). If deferred past 65, it increases 0.7% per month (up to 42% bonus at age 70). Confirm your CPP Statement of Contributions at [My Service Canada Account](https://www.canada.ca/en/employment-social-development/services/my-account.html).

