## Risk Register

### 🔴 High Priority

| Risk | Description | Likelihood | Impact | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **Consulting Revenue Decline** | Client churn, economic downturn, or health limits ability to work | Medium | High | Single largest risk; entire $137,875 gap depends on it |
| **Pension Sustainability** | Defined benefit plan solvency or benefit adjustment | Low | Very High | Confirm plan is fully funded and benefit is indexed |
| **Inflation Erosion** | Fixed pension loses purchasing power over time | High | Medium | At 3% inflation, $45,750 is worth ~$34,000 in 10 years |
| **Partial Year Tax Spike (2026)** | High consulting income Jan–Aug + pension start = elevated 2026 income | High | Medium | Could push into highest federal/provincial bracket |

### 🟡 Medium Priority

| Risk | Description | Likelihood | Impact |
|---|---|---|---|
| **CPP Timing** | Taking CPP at 65 vs. deferring to 70 | Depends on age | Medium |
| **Healthcare Costs** | Loss of employer benefits after retirement | Medium | Medium |
| **OAS Clawback** | If total income exceeds ~$90,997 (2024 threshold), OAS is clawed back | Depends on total income | Medium |
| **RRSP/RRIF Forced Withdrawals** | Mandatory RRIF drawdowns at 71 add taxable income | Low (timing dependent) | Medium |
| **Business Liability Without Corp** | Consulting without corporate structure increases personal exposure | Medium | Low-Medium |

### 🟢 Lower Priority

| Risk | Description |
|---|---|
| **Market Risk** | If retirement savings are invested, sequence-of-returns risk in early retirement years |
| **Currency/Geographic** | If clients pay in USD, exchange rate fluctuation affects net income |
| **IP / Non-compete** | Any clauses from current employer that restrict EA consulting post-retirement |

