## CPP Strategy Decision

| Option | Monthly | Annual | Break-even vs. Age 65 |
|---|---|---|---|
| Age 60 | ~$980 | ~$11,756 | — |
| Age 65 | ~$1,364 | ~$16,375 | Baseline |
| Age 70 | ~$1,937 | ~$23,243 | ~83 years old |

If health is good and you don't need the income immediately at retirement, **deferring CPP to 70 adds $6,868/year** — this could meaningfully reduce your consulting dependency in later years.

