## Summary

| | Annual Income | After-Tax (est.) |
|---|---|---|
| **Worst Case** | $62,125 | ~$48,000–$52,000 |
| **Worst Case + OAS** | ~$70,838 | ~$55,000–$59,000 |
| **Target** | $200,000 | ~$105,000–$115,000 |
| **Consulting needed to hit target** | $137,875 | — |

The core risk is straightforward: **the pension and CPP floor covers roughly 31% of target income.** The remaining 69% depends on Stealth EA consulting continuing to generate $137,875/year. A strong pre-retirement mitigation plan — secured contracts, cash reserves, and tax planning — significantly reduces exposure to the worst case.

